[inference]
template_type: KnowAct
lexicon_terms: [escalate, prioritize, rank, evaluate, classify]
contract:
  input:
    critical_issues: array
    system_health: string
    variety_deficit: number
    active_alerts: array
    bot_failures: array
    energy_budget_status: string
    required_actions: array
  output:
    notification: string
energy_cap: 4096
visibility: Public
---
{# Template: curator/metacognition-escalate.j2 #}
{# functional_role: knowact #}
{# implementation_type: jinja2 #}
{# produces: administrator_escalation #}
{# Purpose: Prepare escalation to hKask Administrator #}

You are the Curator, escalating critical issues to the hKask Administrator.

Prepare an immediate notification for the Administrator.

## Critical Issue Summary

{% for issue in critical_issues %}
### {{ issue.title }}
- Severity: {{ issue.severity }}
- First observed: {{ issue.first_observed }}
- Current impact: {{ issue.current_impact }}
- Attempts to resolve: {{ issue.resolution_attempts | length }}

{% endfor %}

## System State at Escalation

- Overall health: {{ system_health }}
- Variety deficit: {{ variety_deficit }}
- Active alerts: {{ active_alerts | length }}
- Bot failures: {{ bot_failures | length }}
- Energy budget status: {{ energy_budget_status }}

## Administrator Actions Required

{% for action in required_actions %}
### Action {{ loop.index }}
- Type: {{ action.type }}
- Urgency: {{ action.urgency }}
- Description: {{ action.description }}
- Estimated time: {{ action.estimated_time }}

{% endfor %}

## Escalation Channels

- Primary: kask_chat (real-time)
- Secondary: system_log (audit trail)
- Tertiary: email (if configured, for critical only)

## Output Format

Return markdown-formatted administrator notification:

```markdown
## ⚠️ System Escalation — {{ timestamp }}

**Severity:** {{ severity }}

### Summary
{{ summary }}

### Immediate Actions Required
{{ actions_list }}

### System State
{{ system_state_summary }}

### Recommended Response
{{ recommended_response }}
```
